header.gameNote: NCAA Women's Championship pres. by Capital One - National Championship

videos.description: South Carolina coach Dawn Staley expresses her emotions after leading her team to a second national championship.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCW Interview (Dawn Staley: South Carolina wasn't going to be denied) 2022/04/03

videos.headline: Dawn Staley: South Carolina wasn't going to be denied

videos.description: Aliyah Boston and South Carolina defeat the UConn Huskies 64-49 to win the 2022 women's national championship game.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCW Highlight (South Carolina dominates UConn to win national title) 2021/04/03 ESHEET SC

videos.headline: South Carolina dominates UConn to win national title

videos.description: After the 64-49 defeat of UConn, Dawn Staley says No. 1 South Carolina wasn't going to settle for anything less than a national championship.
videos.headline: Staley says Gamecocks 'weren't going to be denied'

videos.description: One year after a heartbreaking loss in the national semifinals left her in tears, South Carolina's Aliyah Boston tells SEC Now she's all smiles now.
videos.headline: Only smiles and tears of joy now for jubilant Boston

videos.description: Destanni Henderson tells SEC Now of her career-high performance for the Gamecocks in the national title game: "I didn't even know I had 26 points."
videos.headline: South Carolina's Henderson: 'I had to let it fly'

videos.description: 1-seed South Carolina races out to a huge lead and holds off the 2-seed Huskies, 64-49, to claim its second national championship in the last five years.
videos.headline: Gamecocks defeat UConn to chase down national title

videos.description: Andraya Carter breaks down why South Carolina is the new dynasty in women's college basketball.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCW Analysis (Why South Carolina is the new dynasty in women’s college basketball) 2022/04/04 FT

videos.headline: Why South Carolina is the new dynasty in women's college basketball
